Six minutes. I'm shocked at how early I am lolol. Now I get to sit here for an hour >:) 

We'd be considered royalty around a century ago. Music and entertainment and the information of the world in our pockets. It's crazy how far we've come.

Oh, and theres a story out there of a kid who locked himself in his room and cried for two weeks after he saw the original 1998(?) Transformers movie because Optimus died. Kids cried leaving the theatres when they saw the movie. It was completely unintentional, too. The writers were just instructed to kill off characters, Optimus especially, because someone mentioned killing off someone for the stakes. Hasbro had no idea what kind of repercussions introducing realistic death into a kid's show with no previous ramifications of realistic death would have, and they made the consequences of the movie permanent. It's hilarious. Ballsy. My favorite moment in cinema history.
